52
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:45,101
that tries to take the big, broad pillars of the genre.

53
00:02:45,481 --> 00:02:46,501
So, you know.

54
00:02:48,222 --> 00:02:51,643
fielding armies and building bases and all that kind of stuff.

55
00:02:52,503 --> 00:02:58,625
And it cuts out all like the micro bloat that's crept into the genre since its heyday in the 90s.

56
00:02:59,605 --> 00:03:06,968
It's designed to be a strategy game as much for fans of the genre as like people who think they don't like strategy games.

57
00:03:07,088 --> 00:03:09,108
It's meant to be really approachable.

58
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:15,070
For a really long time we were using Starcraft meets Mario Kart as the elevator pitch,

59
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:16,391
and I still think that's pretty apt.

