00:33:55,846 --> 00:34:00,028
But for the characters of Tooth and Tail, like the squirrel comes in at like 10 by 10

626
00:34:00,288 --> 00:34:04,711
pixels. It's tiny. This whole thing was lightning fast for this stuff. There wasn't really a

627
00:34:04,791 --> 00:34:06,372
need to ever go back and forth.

628
00:34:07,113 --> 00:34:10,642
uh... as long as i i really tried to capture like the gestalt of the

629
00:34:10,722 --> 00:34:14,712
animation in flash any changes i need to make i could just make in photoshop

630
00:34:16,341 --> 00:34:19,002
So on the surface, it seemed like this was gonna be clumsy,

631
00:34:19,682 --> 00:34:21,203
but it turned out to be pretty efficient.

632
00:34:21,223 --> 00:34:22,823
And then once we took it to production,

633
00:34:22,863 --> 00:34:24,064
I added a few steps that again,

634
00:34:24,104 --> 00:34:25,664
it made it seem like it was gonna be slower,

635
00:34:26,504 --> 00:34:28,245
but it turned out to be even more efficient.

636
00:34:28,545 --> 00:34:30,746
So in production, I would create the rough lines in Flash,

637
00:34:31,146 --> 00:34:32,426
and then I would test those in game.

638
00:34:33,067 --> 00:34:35,748
And then I would clean them up a little bit in Photoshop,

639
00:34:35,808 --> 00:34:37,528
I'd do some like simple color fills,

640
00:34:37,588 --> 00:34:38,929
and I would test those in game.

641
00:34:39,529 --> 00:34:40,689
And then I would bring them back,

642
00:34:40,729 --> 00:34:42,070
I'd do my final shading passes,

643
00:34:42,110 --> 00:34:43,550
and I'd be left with my final artwork.

644
00:34:45,049 --> 00:34:48,011
so i mentioned before about the benefit of uh...

645
00:34:48,611 --> 00:34:50,333
baby steps at this uh... stop

