00:41:24,564 --> 00:41:30,648
a bump map on it that was animated to scroll from the flagpole out to the end of the fabric.

776
00:41:31,768 --> 00:41:34,990
And that was used to kind of create these like tiny undulations that would have been

777
00:41:35,310 --> 00:41:37,352
time-consuming to do like in a rig.

778
00:41:38,372 --> 00:41:44,396
You combine the physical animation of the flag with that texture animation and you get

779
00:41:44,416 --> 00:41:48,038
the final composite, which you know, that works pretty good.

780
00:41:48,999 --> 00:41:49,979
Here it is in-game.

781
00:41:50,199 --> 00:41:50,299
Now.

782
00:41:51,844 --> 00:41:57,087
After a couple more hours of lighting and tweaking values here and there,

783
00:41:57,107 --> 00:41:59,729
kind of trying to fine tune it, this is what we got.

784
00:41:59,929 --> 00:42:05,612
So because we're all kind of used to looking at a lot of game art

785
00:42:05,993 --> 00:42:07,454
and working with this kind of stuff,

786
00:42:09,295 --> 00:42:11,316
I'm sure you can all look at this and say,

787
00:42:11,336 --> 00:42:12,797
I mean, that's pretty cool,

788
00:42:13,617 --> 00:42:16,499
but it doesn't like perfectly match the hand-painted artwork.

789
00:42:17,379 --> 00:42:18,720
And that is true.

790
00:42:18,740 --> 00:42:18,800
But.

791
00:42:22,421 --> 00:42:35,031
I am a pragmatist and I believe in the admittedly unromantic but I think still powerful and

792
00:42:35,152 --> 00:42:38,694
human and kind of poetic notion of good enough.

793
00:42:41,710 --> 00:42:44,093
Good enough has a bad reputation, I think.

794
00:42:45,435 --> 00:42:48,999
When I say good enough, I think maybe a lot of you

795
00:42:49,039 --> 00:42:52,162
can imagine a time when you've had to say,

796
00:42:52,202 --> 00:42:54,805
like, okay, well, this is, we have to ship,

797
00:42:54,845 --> 00:42:55,846
so whatever, good enough.

798
00:42:57,348 --> 00:42:59,250
But I think good enough is like more measured

799
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:00,431
and powerful than that.

800
00:43:02,119 --> 00:43:05,602
So as I said before, I'm a college educator.

801
00:43:06,723 --> 00:43:08,545
And one of the things I tell my students

802
00:43:08,765 --> 00:43:11,889
is not to stress out too badly about finding a job.

803
00:43:11,909 --> 00:43:14,331
In order to get a job, you really only need two things.

804
00:43:14,351 --> 00:43:15,753
You need to have the base level of skill

805
00:43:15,773 --> 00:43:16,714
and just don't be an asshole.

806
00:43:18,490 --> 00:43:21,093
You're gonna enter the industry as a junior artist,

807
00:43:21,133 --> 00:43:23,235
and people know when they hire a junior artist,

808
00:43:24,196 --> 00:43:26,379
there's gonna be some education that needs to happen.

809
00:43:27,179 --> 00:43:28,781
You're not expected to do the work

810
00:43:29,442 --> 00:43:30,883
of a lead artist right out of the gate.

811
00:43:30,943 --> 00:43:32,725
Maybe as a student, you don't even realize

812
00:43:32,745 --> 00:43:34,367
there's a difference between those two things.

813
00:43:35,403 --> 00:43:39,806
You know, but don't worry, because if you try hard,

814
00:43:40,046 --> 00:43:43,369
if you put the hours in learning those core skills,

815
00:43:43,389 --> 00:43:47,651
you try and develop your ability to solve visual problems,

816
00:43:47,691 --> 00:43:49,552
you get out and do some networking,

817
00:43:50,513 --> 00:43:52,054
and you try and be a good person, don't worry,

818
00:43:52,074 --> 00:43:52,835
you're gonna be good enough.

819
00:43:55,052 --> 00:43:58,093
So what's the real philosophy of good enough then?

820
00:43:58,133 --> 00:44:00,674
Good enough is about looking at the whole package

821
00:44:00,734 --> 00:44:01,995
and weighing all options.

822
00:44:02,975 --> 00:44:05,776
I tell my students, I've never hired the best person

823
00:44:05,816 --> 00:44:07,777
who applied for a job when I've been in a studio

824
00:44:07,797 --> 00:44:09,017
and in charge of hiring artists.

825
00:44:09,258 --> 00:44:11,598
I've never hired the best artist,

826
00:44:12,139 --> 00:44:13,439
but I've always hired the best fit.

827
00:44:15,260 --> 00:44:17,780
Certainly, how well someone can practice their craft,

828
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,081
that is a huge part of it.

829
00:44:19,581 --> 00:44:21,742
I don't want to mislead anyone,

830
00:44:21,802 --> 00:44:23,682
but also what kind of person are they?

831
00:44:24,542 --> 00:44:25,683
Are they nice to be around?

832
00:44:25,763 --> 00:44:27,963
Do they express their ideas clearly?

833
00:44:29,204 --> 00:44:31,524
Are they a good problem solver?

834
00:44:31,604 --> 00:44:32,965
Are they self-reliant?

835
00:44:33,005 --> 00:44:33,625
Are they funny?

836
00:44:34,725 --> 00:44:35,626
Are they nurturing?

837
00:44:35,886 --> 00:44:36,966
Are they responsible?

838
00:44:38,106 --> 00:44:39,207
Or are they just an asshole?

